---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About" description="What the Bangpoundulary is and why it has paperwork.">
  <section class="page-intro about-intro">
    <p class="section-kicker">Institutional background</p>
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p>The Bangpoundulary is the public dictionary of Wombology: word-combos that become stranger than their source words intended.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-grid">
    <article class="about-statement">
      <h2>A bit with infrastructure.</h2>
      <p>It began in Discord, acquired case law, gained CI, and now exists as a searchable public record because the bit crossed the infrastructure event horizon.</p>
      <p>The site is generated from Markdown entries in the public GitHub repo. Each entry preserves roots, status, sacrifice analysis, source provenance, and original corpus blocks when available.</p>
    </article>
    <aside class="about-facts" aria-label="Bangpoundulary facts">
      <div><strong>Source</strong><span>Markdown entries</span></div>
      <div><strong>Validation</strong><span>Wombo Law #1</span></div>
      <div><strong>Hosting</strong><span>Static Astro site</span></div>
    </aside>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
